  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Staphylococcus aureus (S. aureus) is the most common pathogen encountered in infections
      associated with orthopedic surgery. StaphVAX® is a bivalent S. aureus types 5 and 8 vaccine
      which contains the purified capsular polysaccharides that have been implicated as a major
      factor in the invasiveness of S. aureus. Immunoprophylaxis by vaccinating against S. aureus
      prior to surgery could provide sufficient antibody concentrations during surgery and the
      wound healing period so as to decrease the risk of S. aureus infection. This study aims to
      demonstrate the immunogenicity and safety of a single dose of StaphVAX in patients who are
      candidates for orthopedic surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
